# Documentation sync (mandatory)

Every roadmap step (sprint) **must** update documentation in the **same change set** as code. Do not mark a step done until indexes and narrative are current.

**Source of truth:** [`docs/lesson-authoring-guide.md`](docs/lesson-authoring-guide.md#documentation-sync-checklist) and [`docs/development-roadmap.md`](docs/development-roadmap.md).

## Minimum checklist

| Surface | Action |
| ------- | ------ |
| `docs/lessons/lesson-NNN-*.md` | Create/update lesson; `Changed Files` lists all doc paths touched |
| `docs/development-roadmap.md` | Step row → `done`; lesson index table at bottom |
| `docs/README.md` | Completed Lessons entry |
| `docs/learning-path.md` | Step link in phase list |
| **`docs/storytelling.md`** | **Always for Track steps:** row in chapter table, narrative in «Как это выглядело», update «Где мы сейчас» / «Что дальше» / intro «после шага NNN» |
| `docs/LOCAL_SETUP.md` | Update when next-step or setup commands change |
| Related lessons | Back-links in Dependencies / «What To Remember» when scope shifts |
| `apps/api/src/**/*.spec.ts` | **Required** with any `apps/api/src/` production change — see [tests-first-api](.cursor/rules/tests-first-api.mdc) |

## Storytelling (do not skip)

Storytelling is **not optional** for completed roadmap steps. It answers *why* in the project story; the lesson answers *how*.

After each step: find the chapter in storytelling TOC → add table row → extend chapter narrative (2–4 sentences) → refresh global status sections.

## Agent behavior

- Before finishing a roadmap task, run through the checklist explicitly (including unit tests for `apps/api` production code).
- If the user asks only for code, still propose doc/storytelling updates or apply them unless the user narrows scope.
- When editing docs-only, keep storytelling consistent with roadmap baseline status.
